Prologue
"Please!" Queen Elvin pleaded, "Don't send her away! She's just a child!" The Ice King sat on his throne, looking down at his wife, with royal advisors standing by. The queen had given birth to a girl. At the thought of this, the Ice King couldn't help but furrow his brow.
The infant girl looked very much like her mother: pale blue eyes, snow-white hair, with a few strands of blue hair点缀. The Ice King thought having a daughter would make him look weak. After all, before this, he had only sons.
"You have only two choices, either kill this child or leave her out in the wilderness. Elvin, this is your punishment." He said her name bitterly, as if it were poison. He always did this.
The Land of Frost was not always a kingdom. It was once divided into two parts, north and south. The north established a non-magical kingdom, while the south was a kingdom full of magical power. Due to the north's greed, the two kingdoms fought an endless war until the south proposed a truce.
The South was already in despair, and the royal family was willing to do anything to stop the bloody conflict. They proposed marrying their only princess to the North, making her the queen of the North and having a son who would become the future king. After that, the South would merge with the North to establish a unified kingdom. The North accepted this proposal, and Princess Elvin thus married Prince Akur.
"Please, my king, for the safety of my child, you can do anything to me, lock me up, exile me, or even kill me." Queen Elvin pleaded, holding her child tightly in her arms.
The Ice King looked down at the queen, filled with contempt. Perhaps, just perhaps, he would have a single moment of mercy for her. After all, this woman had been with him for 22 years, cared for him during his lowest moments, and bore him children.
"Alright. The child can live in the palace." Hearing the Ice King's words, the queen breathed a sigh of relief. "But," he added, "you will be executed."
The royal advisors and Queen Elvin both showed expressions of horror. She slowly lowered her head and looked at the floor. "As you command, my king." She bowed.
The Ice King ordered the royal advisors to take the queen's daughter to one of Elvin's empty rooms. After that, he commanded the guards to take Elvin to the execution ground where all the citizens could see her.
When the guards led her to the execution ground, the citizens saw their only queen—and the kindest queen—about to be executed, and they felt very angry. Some cried, some shouted and tried to attack the guards, and some wanted to know why this was happening; but they all had the same question.
"Let her go!"
"Why are they treating her this way?"
When Elvin approached the wooden pole, the most terrifying person in the kingdom appeared. He was the executioner for the burning punishment. Former Queen Elvin would be burned alive. No one should be subjected to burning, not even criminals. In the Land of Frost, burning was the cruelest punishment.
Elvin was tied to the wooden pole, and the king began to tell how the queen had betrayed them all. The people of the Land of Frost refused to believe it and would never accept the king's words. Then, the executioner lit the wooden pole, and a single tear rolled down the face of this former queen.
"Carly, live on!" The life of Queen Elvin came to an end here.
The hall was silent.
In the south wing of this icy palace, an endless "tapping" sound came from the room on the far left. Past servants were always curious about what was in the room, yet they were too afraid to approach it. The maids walked around the hall, whispering to each other and spreading all sorts of rumors. Some believed that the late wife of the Ice King, Elvin, was living in this room, waiting to be released.
They were completely wrong. Avery thought to himself as he walked toward the south wing, while the servants walked back and forth along the walls, whispering to each other. They had no idea what was inside.
Of course, there were also many rumors about TA, because TA was the only person allowed to enter the room.
Knocked on the door. "Miss Carly, are you inside?" Avery whispered to this complicated door, adorned with snowflakes and crown patterns, symbols of the royal family.
TA didn't know if she would actually let him in this time, which was different from before. I still have bruises from last time. Avery recalled this and couldn't help but laugh. At that time, Carly threw a book at him, but when she realized who it was, she immediately apologized.
A soft sound came from inside the room, as if saying she couldn't go anywhere, just there.
"May I come in?" Avery asked, TA couldn't forget the consequences of entering uninvited last time.
A light sound came again from the room. It seemed to say, "Come in." Avery felt a chill, not sure whether it was from the cold or the voice. Although TA had been there for many years, Avery still found it a bit strange to hear sounds coming from the room.
"I'm coming in," Avery said, slowly opening the door. The scene inside the room was unusual by normal standards, but this was expected. Papers were everywhere in the room. Books were scattered on the floor, the table was broken, and there were many ice sculptures in the room. There were no windows, and there was almost no light. It was also colder here than anywhere else in the palace (which indicated many problems). The room looked as if it had been hit by a blizzard, with everything in a mess.
The girl in the room was curled up in bed, covered with blankets, reading a notebook. A small lantern illuminated the room.
"Which notebook are you reading?" Avery asked, sitting by Carly's bed.
